complexity

Interface Method

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Linear, Timer

    public interface Method
    Implementations of this class should have names suggesting a particular complexity class, and should implement the method and complexity methods in a way that corresponds to the class name. E.g. an implementation of this interface called Linear should implement method such that it has linear (time) complexity (in its parameter n), and implement complexity such that it implements a linear function of its parameter n (the obvious function being f(n)=n).
    Version:
    October 2019
    Author:
    Hugh Osborne

      • complexity

        int complexity(int n)
        Implementations of complexity should implement a function of the parameter n that is appropriate to the implementing class (as indicated by the class's name. E.g. an implementation of complexity in a class called Linear might implement, for example, f(n)=n).
        Parameters:
        n - the "size" of the "problem"
        Returns:
        a value that grows in line with the complexity class modelled
